race.comment: VIVACISSIMO (6) drifted back from her wide draw when resuming last time then hit the line hard to finish third at this track over 1400m. Well placed to feature again. TATSU (4) strode forward early from his wide draw last start over 1462m at Kilmore then fought on gamely to finish second. Stepping up a level this time but on his best form he is capable of a big performance. BRULLEN (7) finished fourth last time out as favourite over 1400m at Mildura, beaten 1.5 lengths. One of the better chances. LEG DRIVE (5) went around a big price first-up but was only beaten 2.5 lengths. He'll be better for that and the extra distance looks right up his alley.
